{{Infobox person | name = Anthony Carrigan | image = | caption = | birth_name = Anthony Carrigan | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1983|1|2}} | birth_place = [[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]], US | occupation = Actor | years_active = 2008–present | known_for = {{plainlist| * ''[[The Forgotten (TV series)|The Forgotten]]'' * ''[[Gotham (TV series)|Gotham]]'' * ''[[Barry (TV series)|Barry]]'' }} }}
'''Anthony Carrigan''' (born January 2, 1983) is an American actor. He is known for portraying [[Victor Zsasz]] in the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX]] television series ''[[Gotham (TV series)|Gotham]]'' and Tyler Davies in ''[[The Forgotten (TV series)|The Forgotten]]''. He is also known for his portrayal of Chechen mobster NoHo Hank in the HBO show ''[[Barry (TV series)|Barry]]''.
Carrigan has had [[alopecia areata]], an [[autoimmune disease]] that causes [[hair loss]], since he was a child.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tvseriesfinale.com/tv-show/barry-hbos-bill-hader-comedy-series-begin-production-spring/|title=Barry: HBO's Bill Hader Comedy Series To Begin Production This Spring - canceled TV shows - TV Series Finale|date=2017-01-14|newspaper=canceled TV shows - TV Series Finale|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2017/01/14/hbo-cinemax-programming-overview-winter-2017-817015/20170114hbo01/|title=Breaking News - HBO/Cinemax Programming Overview - Winter 2017 {{!}} TheFutonCritic.com|website=www.thefutoncritic.com|access-date=2017-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://pl.ign.com/barry/9223/news/nowy-serial-komediowy-od-hbo-zadebiutuje-w-2018-roku|title=Nowy serial komediowy od HBO zadebiutuje w 2018 roku|date=2017-01-14|newspaper=IGN Polska|language=pl-PL|access-date=2017-01-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/eve-harlow-cast-abc-pilot-the-jury-anthony-carrigan-barry-1201704018/|title=Eve Harlow Joins ABC Pilot ‘The Jury’; Anthony Carrigan In HBO’s ‘Barry’|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=2016-02-17|newspaper=Deadline|language=en-US|access-date=2017-01-15}}</ref> He had mild symptoms growing up with only small manageable bald spots, but he started losing more hair in his 20s and has spoken of wearing makeup and fake eyebrows while filming ''[[The Forgotten (TV series)|The Forgotten]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/alexisnedd/gothams-anthony-carrigan-talks-acting-alopecia-and-learning?|title=Gotham's Anthony Carrigan Talks Acting, Alopecia, And Learning To Love His Look|website=BuzzFeed|access-date=2018-08-17}}</ref> He is now known for his complete lack of hair, eyebrows, and eyelashes, and has incorporated this into his career, often being [[typecasting (acting)|typecast]] as television [[villain]]s.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ES7IqPcRFpk|title=Losing His Hair Made Him a Better Actor|date=2016-08-29|newspaper=Great Big Story|language=en-US|access-date=2017-11-20}}</ref>
