{{Infobox royalty |name = Jean-Bédel Bokassa II |image = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1973|11|2|df=y}} |father = [[Jean-Bédel Bokassa]] |mother = Catherine Denguiadé |succession = Crown Prince of the Central African Empire |reign = 4 December 1976 – 21 September 1979 |succession2 = [[House of Bokassa|Head of the House of Bokassa]] |reign2 = 3 November 1996 – present |religion = [[Roman Catholicism]] |house = [[House of Bokassa]] }} Prince '''Jean-Bédel Bokassa, Jr''', or Prince '''Jean-Bédel Bokassa II''' (born 2 November 1973) is a son of [[Jean-Bédel Bokassa]], head of state of the [[Central African Republic]] and its successor state, the [[Central African Empire]], by his sixth wife Catherine Denguiadé, who became Empress on Bokassa's assumption of the throne. Following his father's decision to become Emperor, Jean-Bédel was named, at the age of 4, as [[heir apparent]] with the title of Crown Prince (''prince héritier de Centrafrique''). He was chosen despite having several older brothers and half-brothers. Bokassa I's eldest son by another wife, Georges, was a cabinet minister but Bokassa considered him weak.<ref>Titley, Brian (1997) ''Dark Age: The Political Odyssey of Emperor Bokassa'', McGill-Queen's University Press, {{ISBN|0-7735-1602-6}}, pp. 86–87</ref>
Jean-Bédel was included in Bokassa I's lavish coronation of 4 December 1977, which [[Pope Paul VI]] refused to attend.<ref>Titley, pp. 92–97</ref>
==Honours== ===National dynastic honours=== * {{flagicon|Central African Empire}} [[House of Bokassa]]: Sovereign of the [http://www.medals.org.uk/car/car002.htm Imperial Order of Bokassa] * {{flagicon|Central African Empire}} [[House of Bokassa]]: Sovereign Knight Grand Cordon of the [[Order of Central African Merit|Imperial Order of Central African Merit]]<ref>[http://moimir.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/21_bokassa_021.jpg Moimir]</ref> * {{flagicon|Central African Empire}} [[House of Bokassa]]: Sovereign of the [http://www.medals.org.uk/car/car007.htm Imperial Order of Agricultural Merit] * {{flagicon|Central African Empire}} [[House of Bokassa]]: Sovereign of the [http://www.medals.org.uk/car/car004.htm Imperial Decoration of Recognition]
