{{Proposed deletion/dated |concern = Something isn't right here. The only source I can find is a small page on WikiSource, and the claim of someone living to 116 at that time don't make any sense at all. |timestamp = 20181129160300 |help = }} '''John Cary''' (August 1729 - 2 June 1843) was the colored servant of American Revolutionary War General [[George Washington]].
Cary was born in [[Westmoreland County, Virginia]], in August 1729 and died in [[Washington, D.C.]], 2 June 1843. He was with Washington in the old French war at Braddock's defeat, and accompanied him through the revolutionary struggle.<ref>{{Cite Appletons'|wstitle=Cary, John|year=1900}}</ref>
